Bootstrap cards are specialised designing templates which are used to to present data in systematic and beautiful way with approriate headers and footers it provides a nice user-interface experience and gives better view of data on our websites.

Basic Card
A basic bootstrap card is created with the .card class, and content inside the card has a .card-body class.

Example Code:

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">This is a basic Card</div>
</div>

Header and Footer
The .card-header class builds a heading to the card and the .card-footer class adds a footer to the card:

<div class="card">
  <div class="card_header">This is a Header</div>
  <div class="card_body">Main content</div>
  <div class="card_footer">This is a Footer</div>
</div>

To add a background color  to ourcard, we use classes(
.bg-secondary,
.bg-primary, 
.bg-danger,
.bg-success,
.bg-dark and 
.bg-light,
.bg-info, 
.bg-warning,.)

Use .card-title to add titles to any heading. The .card-text class removes bottom margins for a <p> element if it is the last child inside .card-body. The .card-link class adds a blue color to any link, and a hover effect.

Code:
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h4 class="card-title">This is the title</h4>
    <p class="card-text">I am a Contributor</p>
    <a href="#" class="card-link">Link1</a>
    <a href="#" class="card-link">Link2</a>
  </div>



Card Columns

The .card-columns class creates grid of cards (like pinterest). The layout will automatically adjust as you insert more cards.

Code:

<div class="card-columns">
  <div class="card bg-success">
    <div class="card-body text-center">
      <p class="card-text">Card body</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card bg-primary">
    <div class="card-body text-center">
      <p class="card-text">Card body</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card bg-danger">
    <div class="card-body text-left">
      <p class="card-text">Card body</p>
    </div>
  </div>

 Card Images

 Add .card-img-top or .card-img-bottom to an <img> to place the image at the top or at the bottom inside the card. 
 Code:
 <div class="card" style="width:900px">
  <img class="card-img-top" src="GWOC.png" alt="Image couldn't get loaded">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h4 class="card-title">Anjali</h4>
    <p class="card-text">Card body</p>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Profile name</a>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

  Bootstrap cards can vary in different shapes and sizes with innumerable styles which can be designed in any form.They privide systematic way of representing data in shorter bolder way.
  We see Bootstrap cards in:
  Fashion industry websites
  Portfolios
  Educational websites
  Job websites with peoples' CVs
  
